Durban - Police have arrested four men following a shooting in Tongaat on Tuesday that left one person dead and three others injured.

The four accused, aged between 24 and 37 are expected to make their first appearance in the Verulam Magistrates Court soon. They face charges of murder and attempted murder.
It is alleged that after 2pm, the suspects allegedly fired at a group of men travelling in a black VW Polo along Gopalall Hurbans Road in the Tongaat Central Business District.
Related ArticlesLOOK: One dead, three wounded in Tongaat shootingPolice spokesperson, Lieutenant Colonel Thulani Zwane, said the driver of the Polo lost control of the car and crashed into a tree.
“The driver, Simphiwe Lungani Sithole aged 21, was fatally wounded while the three passengers were injured and taken to hospital for treatment,” Zwane said.AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

“Local police were immediately notified of the shooting and the four suspects were arrested. Their firearms were also seized for the purpose of investigation. Whilst the motive for the shooting is unknown at this stage, detectives are working around the clock to place the suspects before court,” Zwane said.
